1. Create scrollview and put your webView on this scrollView as subview
2. Create UIView and put it under webView as subview of scrollView
3. Create constraints for scroll view (top, leading, trailing, bottom) to subview
4. Create constraints for webView (top, leading, trailing) to scrollView, and bottom constraint to UIView
5. Create constraints for UIView (leading, trailing, bottom) to scrollView and top to webView
6. Create height constraints for webView and UiView
7. Create IBOutlets for height constraints of webView and UiView
8. In delegate method of your webView you can calculate content height and change constraint for your webView 

- (void)webViewDidFinishLoad:(UIWebView *)webView {
    
    CGRect frame = webView.frame;
    frame.size.height = 1;
    webView.frame = frame;
    CGSize fittingSize = [webView sizeThatFits:CGSizeZero];
    frame.size = fittingSize;
    webView.frame = frame;
    
    self.webViewHeightConstraint.constant = fittingSize.height;
}

9. Subscribe your controller to notification 
 
NSNotificationCenter* nc = [NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter];
 
    [nc addObserver:self
           selector:@selector(successfullyRetrievedObjects:)
               name:Constants.ContentHeightDidChaingedNotification
             object:nil];

10. Dynamiccally change height of UIView

- (void) successfullyRetrievedObjects:(NSNotification*) notification {
    
    self.vuukleHeightConstraint.constant = [notification.object floatValue];
}